               <msContents>
                  <msItemStruct>
                     <note type="general">Catalogue no. 26; Nelson collection no. N283.  Pales, the choachyte, is Muhs' Taxpayer 35.  The usual payment for the burial tax on the interment of one individual in the necropolis in the second half of the reign of Ptolemy III was 7 obols.  Pr ("house" or "estate") is often written in place of the masculine definite article pa with the cardinal directions.  In line 4, r pr imnt "the west" is a rare variation on the phrase r ta khast "to the necropolis," which often follows the phrase r.in=w "who was brought" in burial tax receipts.</note>
                     <note type="general">Location: Oriental Institute</note>
                     <note type="general">Pub. status: Published: recto</note>
